sc_cat_item.description: IT Asset Management (ITAM) refers to the strategic and systematic process of acquiring, deploying, maintaining, and disposing of an organization’s IT assets. These assets include hardware (e.g., servers, laptops, and mobile devices), software, network equipment, licenses, and cloud resources.
